RUBY 
    EXCEPTIONAL-HANDLNGI
In Ruby, exception handling is a process which describes a way to handle the error raised in a program

    error : unwanted or unexpected events(generally occurs at runtime), disrupts normal flow of programs and it executions
Syntax:

begin
    raise
          # block where exception raise
     rescue
          # block where exception rescue
end

rescue block as thee name suggests, is used to handles these types of errors 
 ruby also provides a separate class for an exception that is known as an Exception class
    the class contains different types of methods.
